ent-TreasureDatadiskEncrypted-name = encrypted datadisk
ent-TreasureDatadiskEncrypted-desc = An old data disk. Someone savvier than you could unencrypt it and learn something juicy. All you can do is sell it.

ent-TreasureHardDiskDrive-name = hard disk drive
ent-TreasureHardDiskDrive-desc = A disk drive designed for old Earth technology, circa 1980. There's probably some kind of collector who might want to get their paws on this.

ent-TreasureFlopDiskDrive-name = floppy disk drive
ent-TreasureFlopDiskDrive-desc = A drive for reading off info off of floppy disks. Shame that the only things stored on them nowadays are nuclear bomb operations.

ent-TreasureCDDrive-name = CD drive
ent-TreasureCDDrive-desc = A piece of tech for reading data off of CDs. Nowadays that's not the most useful thing, unless you plan on flying somewhere.

ent-TreasureCPUSupercharged-name = supercharged CPU
ent-TreasureCPUSupercharged-desc = Some kind of super alien space tech. Shame all the computers already come with CPUs nowadays.

ent-TreasureSampleTube-name = sample tube
ent-TreasureSampleTube-desc = A glass tube with some sort of goop in it. Looks prone to breaking.

ent-TreasureCoinIron-name = coin
ent-TreasureCoinIron-desc = A flat bit of metal. If it was still in circulation, inflation would've made it worthless. Since it isn't, it's worth enough to keep in a book.

